application_type_full: Tree works: Trees in conservation areas/subject to TPOs
description: T4 1 x Purple plum: remove single pendulous branch directly overhanging Magnolia, back to parent branch (pruning cut of approx. 3cm, branch length to be removed approx. 2m).  Prune remaining branches which are close to the Magnolia back by 1-1.5m to ensure a minimum of 1m clearance; T6 1 x Raywood ash: remove approximately 1-1.5 m from all extremities of heavy, eccentric limb oriented north; T29 False acacia: crown lift to 2.5m over footpathT31 Youngs weeping birch: crown lift young pendulous growth to 2.5m; T47 1 x Purple plum: reduce north and north west oriented limbs by 1-1.5 m; T81 1 x Ash: prune back from adjacent Amelanchier by up to 2m.  Remove single very low downwards-growing branch (north to north-east side), pruning back to the parent branch at a height of about 2m.   Lift low growing pendulous branches all round to 2.5.m, as required to give adequate clearance over beds and footpaths.
